{"ts":"2026-05-29T10:49:38.398Z","host":"Kash-MBA-M3-8GB","mode":"loop","item":"**(P2 · W0) Enforce the full ephemeral-`.claude/` gitignore set fleet-wide + in `doctor` + template.** Broadened 2026-05-29 from the events.jsonl-only case after a second instance of the same class. The bug class: a per-machine ephemeral `.claude/` runtime file that is either untracked-but-unignored (autostash `--include-untracked` grabs it, pop fails → orphan) or outright tracked (the daemon deletes/rewrites it each tick → that tracked change is autostashed and fails to pop → orphan). Concrete instances found: (i) `.claude/backlog-agent-events.jsonl` — gitignored in `backlog-infra` only, untracked elsewhere; fixed during bring-up (added + pushed to 6 repos, stashes dropped). (ii) `.claude/agent-cooldown.json` — **tracked** in dark-mode-safari + sacred-geography (deleted on cooldown-clear → one orphan stash per tick; dark-mode-safari hit 4, sacred-geography 7); fixed 2026-05-29 (untrack + gitignore + push; see Done). **Note `agent-cooldown.json` is missing from `templates/dev-project/.gitignore` entirely.** (iii) `.claude/backlog-agent-failcounts.json` — listed in the template but **untracked-unignored** in backlog-dashboard, dark-mode-safari, predictive-history, sacred-geography (latent autostash co-trigger); only sacred-geography fixed so far. Enforcement: (a) define the canonical ephemeral set in one place and have `doctor` assert every active repo ignores all of it (currently it checks only a subset) — hard-fail on a *tracked* ephemeral file, warn on untracked-unignored; (b) make `templates/dev-project/.gitignore` the superset (add `agent-cooldown.json`); (c) one-shot sweep the remaining repos for the failcounts line. → ties to the D1 telemetry bus (W1), which removes the deeper \"tracked status/history\" variant (see TaizMail item below).","exit_code":143,"duration_ms":746539,"tokens":84185,"tokens_breakdown":{"input":2728,"output":23177,"cache_creation":58280,"cache_read":1391149},"num_turns":29,"session_id":"2271687c-be8c-48f7-a855-50e4220fc029","work_commit":"08f0dfd","full_commit":"08f0dfdd93c010aff0cd1758c9051245b3992004","repo_slug":"kashnoorani/backlog-infra","completed":false,"completed_items":[],"pulled":3,"driver_sha":"ddddc01"}
{"ts":"2026-05-29T10:54:54.662Z","host":"Kash-MBA-M3-8GB","mode":"loop","item":"**(P2 · W1) TaizMail-class orphan-stash leak: tracked status/history files pop-conflict under concurrent cross-machine writes.** Distinct from the gitignore class above — these files are *meant* to be tracked. Found 2026-05-29: TaizMail had **10 orphan stashes** whose content was `M .claude/backlog-history.jsonl` + `M .claude/backlog-status-<host>.local.json` (NOT cooldown/events). Mechanism: the status hook's pre-rebase autostash captures this tick's writes to those tracked files; when origin also changed them (the other machine's tick), the post-rebase pop conflicts → orphaned stash. This is the **\"telemetry riding on commits to shared `.claude/` files\"** root cause the **D1 telemetry bus (W1, COMMITTED)** is designed to eliminate — move per-tick liveness/status/history off git onto D1 so concurrent ticks stop colliding on these files. Until then it's intermittent (TaizMail: ~10 over 2h, not every tick). 10 junk stashes left in place on TaizMail's M1 clone (user opted: backlog item only); inspect-per-stash + drop when the W1 fix lands. **Sacred-geography note:** during the cooldown fix, one pre-existing (06:28, daemon-orphaned) `docs/Backlog.md` autostash was caught by a `stash clear` and re-anchored as `refs/orphan-rescue/backlog-2026-05-29T0628Z` (tag `orphan-rescue-backlog-0628`) — audited to contain no open/blocked items (compacted verbose prose only); drop the rescue ref once confirmed unneeded.","exit_code":1,"duration_ms":451,"tokens":0,"tokens_breakdown":{"input":0,"output":0,"cache_creation":0,"cache_read":0},"num_turns":1,"session_id":"f6506fb0-39bf-439a-83e9-0db178b8d528","work_commit":"98de6d9","full_commit":"98de6d91dd68e033da017ccea34f24a072758c98","repo_slug":"kashnoorani/backlog-infra","completed":false,"completed_items":[],"pulled":0,"driver_sha":"ddddc01"}
